⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Dan Davis & Pete the Cat
node H1 · H1 · ⟦Dan Davis & Pete the Cat:H1:dd99ee⟧

WHO   — Daniel Boone Davis, a gifted engineer who invents household robots, and his ginger tomcat Pete, who in winter insists on being let out every door in the house, certain that one of them must open onto summer.
WHAT  — The heart of The Door into Summer — an inventor cheated out of his company by his partner and his fiancée, dumped into cold sleep, who claws back his life through the Long Sleep and a quiet, lawful experiment in time travel.
WHERE — 1970 and 2000 California — Los Angeles, the Hired Girl and Flexible Frank workshops, the cold-sleep sanctuaries — looped together by time travel into a single set-right life.
WHY   — Because some things are worth getting back — honest credit for your work, the girl who actually loved you, and your cat — and because Dan, like Pete, refuses to believe there isn't a door into summer somewhere if you just keep trying them all.
HOW   — By engineering, by cold-sleep across thirty years, by a one-shot time machine, and by patient, methodical resolve — fixing the future by going back and doing it right.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  Somewhere there's a door into summer — and a smart man keeps trying doors until he finds it.

